# MyWeightHelperApp

Welcome to MyWeightHelperApp! This is a simple Blazor application for calculating BMI (Body Mass Index) based on height and weight input.

## Prerequisites

Before running the application and tests, ensure that you have the following installed:

- [.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) for building and running .NET projects.
- [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) or any other preferred code editor.

## Running the Application

To run the MyWeightHelperApp Blazor project:

1. Open a terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the root directory of the MyWeightHelperApp project.
3. Run the following command to build and run the application:
    ```
    dotnet run
    ```
4. Open a web browser and navigate to `https://localhost:5001/myweighthelper` to access the application.

## Running the Tests

The MyWeightHelperApp.Tests project contains unit tests for the WeightHelper class using xUnit.

To run the tests:

1. Open a terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the root directory of the MyWeightHelperApp.Tests project.
3. Run the following command to execute the tests:
    ```
    dotnet test
    ```
4. The test results will be displayed in the terminal, indicating the number of tests passed, failed, and skipped.

